# Certificate System Upgrade & Bug Fix Plan

This implementation plan outlines the upgrades, fixes, and testing strategies for the `pharmacozyme-certs` system, discovering and addressing critical bugs in ID generation and sorting logic, and providing a robust testing framework.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The current length of generating certificate IDs is limited to 4 hexadecimal characters (`uuidv4().slice(0, 4)`), which provides only 65,536 unique combinations. **This poses a high risk of ID collisions during batch generation**. We propose upgrading this to at least 6 or 8 characters (`uuidv4().split('-')[0]`), which provides over 4 billion combinations. **This will change the format of future IDs from `PZ-2026-XXXX` to `PZ-2026-XXXXXXXX`**. Please let me know if this format change is acceptable!

## Proposed Changes

---

### ID Generation & Collisions

Currently, multiple IDs generated concurrently could potentially overlap due to the short UUID slice. We will upgrade the generation length to increase entropy.

#### [MODIFY] [generate/route.ts](file:///d:/Claude%20Code%20workspace/PZ%20Certificate%20Verification%20System/pharmacozyme-certs/app/api/certificates/generate/route.ts)
- Update `certId` creation to use an 8-character slice: `uuidv4().split('-')[0].toUpperCase()`.

---

### Hexadecimal Sorting Logic Bug

Currently, the arrays of participants are sorted using JavaScript's base-10 `parseInt` on hexadecimal strings. For example: `parseInt("1B9D")` returns `1`, and `parseInt("A2F1")` returns `NaN`. This completely breaks the deterministic syncing of Google Sheets data and certificate generation lists.

#### [MODIFY] [generate/route.ts](file:///d:/Claude%20Code%20workspace/PZ%20Certificate%20Verification%20System/pharmacozyme-certs/app/api/certificates/generate/route.ts)
- Change the sorting comparison logic to parse as base 16: `parseInt(..., 16)`, or convert it to use `.localeCompare()` for robust alphabetic hex sorting.

#### [MODIFY] [sync/route.ts](file:///d:/Claude%20Code%20workspace/PZ%20Certificate%20Verification%20System/pharmacozyme-certs/app/api/sheets/sync/route.ts)
- Apply the same base-16 `parseInt` or `.localeCompare()` fix to the `firebaseToSheets` syncing sort logic.

---

### Verification Resiliency

If a user manually types a certificate ID on the verification page using lowercase letters (e.g. `pz-2026-1b9d`), Firebase will return a 404 because Firebase queries are case-sensitive and the ID is stored as `PZ-2026-1B9D`.

#### [MODIFY] [verify/route.ts](file:///d:/Claude%20Code%20workspace/PZ%20Certificate%20Verification%20System/pharmacozyme-certs/app/api/verify/route.ts)
- Coerce `certId` to uppercase: `certId = certId.toUpperCase()` before executing the Firestore `where("uniqueCertId", "==", certId)` query.

---

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> Regarding the ID format: Since past IDs are 4 characters (e.g. `PZ-2026-1B9D`), they will continue to work perfectly. For new operations, should I update the ID part to 8 characters (e.g. `PZ-2026-A1B2C3D4`) or explicitly 6 characters? 

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Review Typescript Build (`npm run build`) to ensure no implicit `any` bugs or compilation warnings are introduced. 
- Fix any local testing scripts (like `test-api.js`) which currently use hardcoded backend IPs (`192.168.18.165`) and update them to rely on environmental variables or generic loops.

### Manual Verification
- Generate a batch of test certificates and ensure the Google Sheet sync populates the cells sequentially according to the updated Base-16 logic.
- Perform a simulated search query using all lowercase characters (`pz-xxxx`) and verify the 200 HTTP code returns the payload gracefully.
- Validate the new ID length works well through the full end-to-end verification and email dispatch via Resend.
